I will produce a minimal fix that addresses the likely issue: In the else branch, before the while loop, we should check if objectType is a function type and if so, get its instance type and use its prototype chain. 

Fix:
```
} else {
  // classes
  // If objectType is a function type, we need to look at its instance's prototype
  if (objectType.isFunctionType() && objectType.toObjectType() != null) {
    ObjectType instanceType = ((FunctionType) objectType).getInstanceType();
    if (instanceType != null) {
      objectType = instanceType.getImplicitPrototype();
    }
  }
  while (objectType != null && !objectType.hasOwnProperty(propName)) {
    objectType = objectType.getImplicitPrototype();
  }
}
```

